summary:
7. Reminds States of their obligation to implement measures under resolutions 1521 (2003) and 1532 (2004), particularly freezing assets of persons designated by the Committee;

8. Re-establishes the Panel of Experts until 21 June 2005 to:
    (a) Conduct a follow-up assessment mission to investigate and compile a report on implementation and violations;
    (b) Assess the impact and effectiveness of measures imposed by resolution 1532 (2004);
    (c) Assess progress towards meeting conditions;
    (d) Assess humanitarian and socio-economic impact;
    (e) Report to the Council through the Committee by 7 June 2005;
    (f) Provide a preliminary report by 21 March 2005;

9. Requests the Secretary-General to appoint experts and make necessary arrangements;

10. Calls upon UNMIL and other UN Missions to assist the Committee and Panel of Experts;

11. Calls upon States and the National Transitional Government to cooperate with the Panel;

12. Requests the Secretary-General to submit a report by 7 June 2005 on progress made;

13. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
